Source: Dictionary of Kiwi Slang, A
Author:
Vol / Page: McGILL
Edition: 40
Quote: duckshove to cheat or pass responsibility on to someone else, perceived as a typical bureaucratic trick; eg `The public is always complaining of duckshoving in that department.' Originally cabbies jumping the queue in mid-C19 Melbourne cab ranks. ANZ.
